#summary Storing (creating or updating) a persistent object without using transactions.

{{{
                // Create an object if not already in the repository
                SimplePersistent persistentObject = new SimplePersistent("1").setValue("Initial");
                repository.store(persistentObject);
                
                persistentObject = (SimplePersistent) repository.restore("1");
                
                // A second call to store will update the object.
                persistentObject.setValue("First Value");
                repository.store(persistentObject);
}}}

 # Restore the persistent object or create a new instance if this is a new object. 
 # Update the object properties. 
 # Create or update the object by invoking the store method.

If the repository contains another object with the same identity, the object is [NonTransactionalUpdate updated]. Otherwise, a new persistent object is [NonTransactionalCreate created].

